      • getProperty

        public List<Property> getProperty()
        Translates into ODBCSourceAttributes Gets the value of the property property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the property property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getProperty().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list Property

      • getODBCDataSource

        public List<ODBCDataSource> getODBCDataSource()
        Gets the value of the odbcDataSource property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the odbcDataSource property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getODBCDataSource().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list ODBCDataSource
